ViewSet: Handles the logic for CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) on your model. It defines what data to retrieve and how to process requests.

CompanyViewSet: This class inherits from ModelViewSet, which provides default implementations for CRUD operations.

queryset: Specifies the set of data to be used. Here, it's all instances of the Company model.

serializer_class: Defines which serializer to use for converting model instances to and from JSON.
